kubectl Commands
-----------------

    alias k=kubectl --> create an alias for kubectl
    --> To set it up, open Terminal:  $ vi ~/.bashrc
                                      Add the following line:  alias k=kubectl
                                      $ source ~/.zshrc
                                      Open new Terminal and type:  k --help


    kubectl --> check kubectl help
    kubectl --help --> check kubectl help
    k --help --> check kubectl help

    kubectl version --> check kubectl version
    kubectl cluster-info --> check cluster info

    kubectl get all --> retrieve information about Kubernetes Pods, Deployments, Services, etc.
    kubectl get pods --> retrieve information about Kubernetes Pods
    kubectl get deployments --> retrieve information about Kubernetes Deployments
    kubectl get services --> retrieve information about Kubernetes Services
    kubectl get nodes --> retrieve information about Kubernetes Nodes

    kubectl run [container-name] --image=[image-name] --> simple way to create a Deployment for a Pod
    kubectl port-forward [pod-name] [local-port]:[pod-port] --> enable Pod container to be called externally
    kubectl expose pod [pod-name] --port=[port] --name=[service-name] --> expose a pod for a Deployment/Pod
    kubectl create [resource] --> create a resource
    kubectl apply [resource] --> apply a resource

